      <section eId="sec_CC-3346">
        <num>CC 3346</num>
        <heading>3346.  Place of recordation; duty of the recorder</heading>
        <subsection eId="CC-3346__subsec_A">
          <num>A.</num>
          <content>
            <p>An instrument creating, establishing, or relating to a mortgage or privilege over
an immovable, or the pledge of the lessor's rights in the lease of an immovable and its rents,
is recorded in the mortgage records of the parish in which the immovable is located. All other
instruments are recorded in the conveyance records of that parish.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="CC-3346__subsec_B">
          <num>B.</num>
          <content>
            <p>The recorder shall maintain in the manner prescribed by law all instruments that
are recorded with him.</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <authorialNote marker="source">
          <p>Source: https://www.legis.la.gov/legis/Law.aspx?d=110395</p>
        </authorialNote>
      </section>
